author: CBS Dallas / Fort Worth
title: 1 Dead In Lake Highlands Home Invasion
text:
Follow CBSDFW.COM: Facebook | Twitter 
DALLAS (CBSDFW.COM) – Dallas Police say two suspects are wanted in deadly home invasion at an apartment in the 9600 block of Ferris Branch Boulevard in Lake Highlands around 3:30 p.m. Monday. 
One victim was shot to death. Another victim was shot in the leg and being treated at the hospital. 
The woman who was shot in the leg was in the parking lot when police arrived and she directed officers to apartment 318. That’s where officers found Jason Ali Edwards, 39, deceased from gunshot wounds. A canvass of the area and witnesses interviewed stated that a silver four-door vehicle was seen leaving the complex after the shooting. (©2017 CBS Local Media, a division of CBS Radio Inc.
